CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 13, 1963, pg. 1, reads: "UNPC Boosters - Linda Johnson (left), 410 N. Neville St., and Karen Mosely, 634 Kirkpatrick St., hold aloft new green and white buttons which members of the United Protest Committee are sporting around the city. Miss Johnson is a member of the NAACP and attends Pitt's graduate school of social work.  Miss Mosely is a graduate of Robert Morris Business School. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Linda Johnson and Karen Mosely holding buttons inscribed "Marshall - The United Negro Protest Committee" and "Let's March - The United Negro Protest Committee"
